dren and society than good.The Perversion of Youth critiques the current system and its methods for treating and categorizing juveniles, and calls for a major reevaluation of how these cases should be managed in the future. Through an analysis of the history of the problem and an empirical review of the literature, including specific cases and their outcomes, DiCataldo demonstrates that current practices are based more on our collective fears and moral passions than on any supportive science or sound policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aTeenage sex offendersxPsychology. 0aTeenage sex offendersxRehabilitation. 4aDiCataldo. 4aMany. 4aand. 4abeing. 4acautions. 4achildren. 4adeal. 4adoing. 4aempirical. 4agood. 4aharm. 4ahave. 4ajuvenile. 4amore. 4aoffenders. 4asociety. 4astrategies. 4asupport. 4athan. 4atoday. 4aused. 4awith. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Developmental / Adolescent.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814785225423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814785225.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK